2011-08-03T10:49:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/ghana-meteorological-agency-s-rainfall-report-july-21-31-table-.html
The following are rainfall figures
for  Ghana , the world’s second biggest cocoa producer, from July
21 to July 31, according to the  Ghana  Meteorological Agency.  The western region, which includes Sefwi Bekwai and Bogoso,
is the country’s largest growing area for the chocolate
ingredient, accounting for 55 percent of output, according to
the Ghana Cocoa Board.  The Ashanti region accounts for about 18 percent of
production, while Brong Ahafo generates 9.3 percent, the eastern
region 8.6 percent and the central region 8.8 percent.  The  Ivory Coast , which neighbors Ghana, is the world’s
largest cocoa producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
